        "Description": "",
        "DOI": "",
        "Main Related Publication": "Post-combustion carbon capture unit based on Aqualung hollow-fiber membrane technology, which uses amine-embedded membranes to selectively permeate CO2 under vacuum (0.4 bar) from flue gas. The process achieves 90% CO2 recovery with electricity consumption for vacuum generation and permeate recompression as the only energy inputs.",
        "References": "[1] https://aqualung-cc.com/ \n [2] Janakiram et. al https://doi.org/10.1016/j.cej.2020.127405  \n [3] M-B Hägg et al. Energy Procedia 114 ( 2017 ) 6150 – 6165",
